=== Multi-Cycle Tinker CPU (Programming Assignment 9) ===

This project implements a multi-cycle Tinker processor in SystemVerilog.

--- Architecture ---

The processor uses a 5-stage FSM:

  S_IF  (Instruction Fetch)   — fetch 32-bit instruction from memory at PC
  S_ID  (Instruction Decode)  — decode fields, read registers into pipeline latches
  S_EX  (Execute)             — ALU computes result; branches update PC here
  S_MEM (Memory Access)       — loads/stores/call/return access data memory
  S_WB  (Write Back)          — write ALU result or loaded data to register file

Cycle counts per instruction type:
  ALU/FPU, MOV1, MOV2        : IF → ID → EX → WB           (4 cycles)
  Branch (BR, BRR, BRNZ, ...) : IF → ID → EX → IF           (3 cycles)
  Load  (MOV rd, (rs)(L))    : IF → ID → EX → MEM → WB     (5 cycles)
  Store (MOV (rd)(L), rs)    : IF → ID → EX → MEM → IF     (4 cycles)
  CALL / RETURN               : IF → ID → EX → MEM → IF     (4 cycles)
  PRIV (halt)                 : IF → ID → EX → [frozen]     (3+ cycles)

The hlt output is asserted in EX when a PRIV L=0 instruction is decoded,
and stays asserted forever (the FSM freezes on the next cycle).

--- File Layout ---

  tinker.sv         Top-level file (required by Gradescope); contains:
                      - memory_module
                      - reg_file_module
                      - fp_add / fp_sub / fp_mul / fp_div
                      - alu_fpu
                      - tinker_core  (top-level module with FSM)

  test/
    tb_tinker.sv    Testbench covering: ADD, arithmetic/logic, BRNZ loop,
                    load/store, and CALL/RETURN.

  sim/              Waveform output (.vcd) goes here after simulation.
  vvp/              Compiled simulation binary goes here.

--- How to Compile and Run ---

From the 9prog/ directory:

  # Compile
  iverilog -g2012 -o vvp/tb_tinker.vvp test/tb_tinker.sv tinker.sv

  # Run simulation (prints pass/fail to stdout)
  vvp vvp/tb_tinker.vvp

  # Optional: open waveform
  gtkwave sim/tb_tinker.vcd

--- Module Interface ---

  module tinker_core (
      input  clk,
      input  reset,
      output logic hlt
  );

  - reset is active-high synchronous; initializes PC to 0x2000 and
    register 31 to MEM_SIZE (524288 = 512 KB).
  - hlt goes high when a PRIV L=0 (halt) instruction completes EX.
  - Memory is 512 KB, byte-addressed, little-endian.
